The paper discusses feature extraction methods for biological sequences and their application in machine learning tasks such as classification. This topic falls under the intersection of computer science and biology, making cs.BIO a likely category. The paper also introduces a new stability measure for motif extraction methods, which involves evaluating the robustness of the methods in the face of perturbations in the input data. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science), which deal with similar topics. Finally, the paper uses an object-property table to represent the extracted motifs, which is a common data structure in databases and data mining. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to categories such as cs.DB (databases).
